-- Everton Beats Swansea 3-0 to Tie Chelsea for Premier League Lead
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-09-22T13:42:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-22/everton-beats-swansea-3-0-to-tie-chelsea-for-premier-league-lead.html
Everton beat Swansea 3-0 to move
into a tie for first place with Chelsea in English soccer’s
Premier League.  Victory Anichebe, Kevin Mirallas and  Marouane Fellaini 
scored the goals at Swansea’s Liberty Stadium. Everton and
Chelsea both have 10 points, with the Blues hosting Stoke later
today.  Swansea’s Nathan Dyer was sent off for receiving two yellow
cards in the first 12 minutes after coming on as a halftime
substutite.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  